<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>What Most People Get Wrong</h2>

  <p>
    <strong>Buying more tools.</strong> Most experienced gardeners already have what they need, and lower-quality duplicates rarely get used.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Choosing novelty items.</strong> Interesting gifts are not always practical, and often get ignored after the first season.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Ignoring how the person actually gardens.</strong> The best gift fits their system, not a generic idea of gardening.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="calloutBox">
  <h2>What Most People Should Actually Gift</h2>

  <p>
